# Project Structure Guide

This is a React-based bandsaw search application. Here's the key structure:

## Main Application Files
- The application entry point is [src/index.tsx](mdc:src/index.tsx)
- Main application component is [src/App.tsx](mdc:src/App.tsx)
- Core layout components:
  - [src/Header.tsx](mdc:src/Header.tsx) - Application header
  - [src/Body.tsx](mdc:src/Body.tsx) - Main content area with styling in [src/Body.css](mdc:src/Body.css)

## Data Management
- Main data file: [data/bandsaws.json](mdc:data/bandsaws.json)
- Data processing utilities:
  - [process_amperage.ts](mdc:process_amperage.ts) - Processes amperage data in bandsaw records
  - [data/import-bandsaws.ts](mdc:data/import-bandsaws.ts) - Data import utilities

## Configuration
- Project configuration in [package.json](mdc:package.json)
- Code style configuration in [.prettierrc](mdc:.prettierrc) and [.editorconfig](mdc:.editorconfig)

## Development Guidelines
1. All React components should be placed in the `src/components` directory
2. Data processing scripts should be placed in the `data` directory
3. Follow the existing TypeScript patterns for type definitions
4. Use the provided Prettier and EditorConfig settings for consistent code formatting
